<div id="text"><p>"I live in Paddington and work on my favourite road in London, Golborne Road. Just off the famous Portobello a tourist hotspot, Golborne manages to maintain that local feel which make it home to the best street food in London and an array of small Portuguese and Moroccan cafes. I stop for a hot chocolate and “coxinha” almost everyday and language barrier aside have a great chat with the owner of Cafe Porto before I start my day…he reminds me of Geppetto. Perfect location, rich culture and delicious affordable food. What’s more is the route i cycle to work takes me down the canal through the idyllic Little Venice which looks beautiful in every season."</p></div>